>
  <Nav />

  <main class="compare">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="compare-article">
        <header class="compare-header">
          <a href="/compare/" class="back-link">← All comparisons</a>
          <span class="compare-eyebrow">Comparison · Last verified {lastVerified}</span>
          <h1>Stripe vs PayPay for Japan Businesses</h1>
          <p class="compare-lead">
            This isn't a typical either/or comparison. Stripe and PayPay solve
            fundamentally different problems: online payments vs in-person QR
            codes. The question isn't "which one" but whether you need one or
            both for your Japan payment stack.
          </p>
          <div class="compare-meta">
            <span>By <a href="/about/" rel="author">Matt Ketchum</a></span>
            <span>·</span>
            <span>Tokyo</span>
            <span>·</span>
            <span>~8 min read</span>
          </div>
        </header>

        <aside class="tldr" aria-label="Verdict summary">
          <h2 class="tldr__heading">Verdict</h2>
          <div class="verdict">
            <div class="verdict__side">
              <h3>Stripe wins for</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Online stores, SaaS products, subscription billing</li>
                <li>Digital service invoicing, website payments</li>
                <li>Foreign founders needing easy merchant account setup</li>
                <li>Businesses processing international customer cards</li>
                <li>Developer-controlled payment experiences</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="verdict__side">
              <h3>PayPay wins for</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>In-person retail, restaurants, cafes, events</li>
                <li>Physical location QR code payments</li>
                <li>Japanese consumer-facing businesses</li>
                <li>B2C where 60M+ PayPay users matter</li>
                <li>Lower per-transaction costs for in-person sales</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="verdict__conclusion">
            <strong>You probably need both.</strong> Stripe for your digital payment layer.
            PayPay for in-person. The question is never Stripe vs PayPay - it's which
            in-person QR solution and which online payment processor to use.
          </p>
        </aside>

        <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
